  <description value="Root object of a linear history, i.e. time series structure. This is a generic class whose type parameter must be a descendant of `ITEM_STRUCTURE`, ensuring that each Event in the `_events_` of a given instance is of the same structural type, i.e. `ITEM_TREE`, `ITEM_LIST` etc.&#xA;&#xA;For a periodic series of events, period will be set, and the time of each Event in the History must correspond; i.e. the `EVENT._offset_` must be a multiple of period for each Event. Missing events in a period History are however allowed. "/>
  <jurisdiction>
    <coding>
      <system value="http://unstats.un.org/unsd/methods/m49/m49.htm"/>
      <code value="001"/>
    </coding>
  </jurisdiction>
